cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.MM

The paper discusses the analysis of smartphone network traffic to profile users based on their gender, profession, and age group. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with privacy and security concerns related to user data. Additionally, the paper also involves machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of encryption and statistical analysis of traffic also relates to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CY) and software development (cs.SD). Finally, the paper also mentions the sharing of multimedia over the internet, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
